<br>
I've no played a Ranger yet, but my friend (currently a level 24 Ranger) considers celtic dual a grand waste of time, and says the armor is so crappy that their average life expectancy in melee is only marginally better than the casters'. Scouts, well... you've listened to all my rants so far, I don't need to sit here and make the same redundant argument. It's a safe assumption that archery classes will get fixed, I just hope that they fix the archery part and not try to turn us into melee classes.<br>
<br>
Personally, I just deleted my scout. There's 10000000000000 of them on my server, and 99% of them are utterly clueless and make it exceedingly difficult for those of us who function well and know our role within a group to get one. I really love archery and the idea of being able to play like a sniper, but not if it's also condemndation to a life of barely killing blues by myself and having to turn and run to a guard every third battle because I missed critical shot.<br>
